(block_type='text', text='{\n    "reasoning": "The core tasks are generating the interface matching the testbench and significantly improving the testbench to incorporate advanced, queue-based, synchronous error logging as mandated for sequential logic.\\n\\n**Interface Generation:**\\n1. The golden testbench instantiates `TopModule` with ports: `clk` (input), `load` (input), `ena` (input [1:0]), `data` (input [99:0]), and `q` (output [99:0]).\\n2. The interface must precisely match this structure, using `logic` types for all ports, regardless of the input specification ambiguity.\\n\\n**Testbench Improvement Strategy:**\\n1. **Sequential Logic Handling:** Since `TopModule` is sequential, the queue-based mechanism (Requirement 1) must be implemented.\\n2. **Queue Definition:** I define separate queues for inputs (`data_q`, `ena_q`, `load_q`), outputs (`q_dut_q`, `q_ref_q`), and inputs/controls (`data_q`, `ena_q`, `load_q`). I will also queue the clock and a conceptual \'reset\' state (though no explicit reset is used, it\'s good practice for structure).\\n3. **MAX_QUEUE_SIZE:** Set to 10 as per instructions, controlling log size.\\n4. **Synchronous Logging:** The queue push/pop and mismatch checking must occur within `always @(posedge clk, negedge clk)` to align with the clocking domain of the verification.\\n5. **Verification Logic:** The original matching condition `tb_match = ( { q_ref } === ( { q_ref } ^ { q_dut } ^ { q_ref } ) )` is maintained, which simplifies to `tb_match = (q_ref === q_dut)`.\\n6. **Error Tracking & Display:** The original `stats1` structure is kept for total counting. The new queue logic handles detailed logging of the *first* error. The original `final` block is replaced to output the required success/failure message based on `stats1.errors` and `stats1.errortime` (which tracks the first error time).\\n7. **Data Formatting:** For 100-bit signals, only HEX display will be used in the queue loop, as the width exceeds 64 bits, adhering to the instruction.\\n8. **Functionality Preservation:** All original stimulus generation, module instantiations (`stimulus_gen`, `RefModule`, `TopModule`), and the core error counting logic (`stats1.errors++` when `!tb_match`) are preserved.\\n\\n**Syntax Advice:** Use `logic` type consistently. Ensure the queue management (deletion/pushing) is correctly sequenced within the clocked block to prevent race conditions during error capture. When displaying large vectors (100 bits), using `%h` is appropriate, and the requirement to display binary is bypassed for signals > 64 bits.",\n    "interface": "module TopModule(\\n    input clk,\\n    input load,\\n    input [1:0] ena,\\n    input [99:0] data,\\n    output [99:0] q\\n);\\nendmodule",\n    "testbench": "`timescale 1 ps/1 ps\\n`define OK 12\\n`define INCORRECT 13\\n\\n// Stimulus Generator remains unchanged as per requirement 1\\nmodule stimulus_gen (\\n\\tinput clk,\\n\\toutput reg load,\\n\\toutput reg[1:0] ena,\\n\\toutput reg[99:0] data\\n);\\n\\t\\talways @(posedge clk)\\n\\t\\t\\tdata <= {$random,$random,$random,$random};\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tinitial begin\\n\\t\\t\\tload <= 1;\\n\\t\\t\\t@(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\t\\t@(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\t\\t@(posedge clk);\\n\\t\\t\\trepeat(4000) @(posedge clk, negedge clk) begin\\n\\t\\t\\tload <= !($random & 31);\\n\\t\\t\\tena <= $random;\\n\\t\\t\\tend;\\n\\t\\t\\t#1 $finish;\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tendmodule\\n\\nmodule tb();\\n\\t\\t// Stats structure maintained from golden testbench\\n\\t\\ttypedef struct packed {\\n\\t\\t\\tint errors;\\n\\t\\t\\tint errortime;\\n\\t\\t\\tint errors_q;\\n\\t\\t\\tint errortime_q;\\n\\t\\t\\tint clocks;\\n\\t\\t} stats;\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tstats stats1;\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t// --- Queue-based simulation mismatch display setup (Requirement 1) ---\\n\\t\\treg [99:0] input_data_q [$];\\n\\t\\treg [99:0] got_output_q [$];\\n\\t\\treg [99:0] golden_output_q [$];\\n\\t\\treg [1:0] ena_q [$];\\n\\t\\treg load_q [$];\\n\\t\\treg [99:0] data_q [$];\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t// Since the module is sequential, we queue inputs/outputs\\n\\t\\tlocalparam MAX_QUEUE_SIZE = 10; // Set to 10 as per instructions\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t// Signal declarations\\n\\t\\treg clk=0;\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t// Inputs to DUT/Reference\\n\\t\\tlogic load;\\n\\t\\tlogic [1:0] ena;\\n\\t\\tlogic [99:0] data;\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t// Outputs from DUT/Reference\\n\\t\\tlogic [99:0] q_ref;\\n\\t\\tlogic [99:0] q_dut;\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t// Verification Signals\\n\\t\\twire tb_match;\\n\\t\\twire tb_mismatch = ~tb_match;\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t// Clock generation\\n\\t\\tinitial forever\\n\\t\\t\\t#5 clk = ~clk;\\n\\n\\t\\t// Waveform dumping setup (kept from original)\\n\\t\\tinitial begin \\n\\t\\t\\t$dumpfile(\\"wave.vcd\\");\\n\\t\\t\\t$dumpvars(1, stim1.clk, tb_mismatch ,clk,load,ena,data,q_ref,q_dut );\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\n\\t\\t// Stimulus Generator Instance\\n\\t\\tstimulus_gen stim1 (\\n\\t\\t\\t.clk, .load, .ena, .data\\n\\t\\t);\\n\\n\\t\\t// DUT/Reference Instantiations (Kept from original)\\n\\t\\tRefModule good1 (\\n\\t\\t\\t.clk, .load, .ena, .data, .q(q_ref) );\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tTopModule top_module1 (\\n\\t\\t\\t.clk, .load, .ena, .data, .q(q_dut) );\\n\\n\\t\\t// Task wait_for_end_of_timestep (Kept from original)\\n\\t\\tbit strobe = 0;\\n\\t\\ttask wait_for_end_oftimestep;\\n\\t\\t\\trepeat(5) begin\\n\\t\\t\\tstrobe <= !strobe;  // Try to delay until the very end of the time step.\\n\\t\\t\\t@(strobe);\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tendtask\\n\\n\\t\\t// Synchronous Verification and Queue Management\\n\\t\\talways @(posedge clk, negedge clk) begin\\n\\t\\t\\tstats1.clocks++;\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t// 1. Queue Management (FIFO behavior)\\n\\t\\t\\tif (input_data_q.size() >= MAX_QUEUE_SIZE - 1) begin\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tinput_data_q.delete(0);\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tgot_output_q.delete(0);\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tgolden_output_q.delete(0);\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tena_q.delete(0);\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tload_q.delete(0);\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tdata_q.delete(0);\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t// 2. Push current values into queues\\n\\t\\t\\tinput_data_q.push_back(data);\\n\\t\\t\\tena_q.push_back(ena);\\n\\t\\t\\tload_q.push_back(load);\\n\\t\\t\\tdata_q.push_back(data);\\n\\t\\t\\tgot_output_q.push_back(q_dut);\\n\\t\\t\\tgolden_output_q.push_back(q_ref);\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t// 3. Check for first mismatch and log (Requirement 1.1, 1.3)\\n\\t\\t\\tif (!tb_match) begin\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tif (stats1.errors == 0) stats1.errortime = $time;\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tstats1.errors++;\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t$display(\\"========================================================\\");\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t$display(\\"!!! FIRST MISMATCH DETECTED AT TIME %0t !!!\\", $time);\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t$display(\\"Last %0d cycles of simulation recorded:\\", input_data_q.size());\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tfor (int i = 0; i < input_data_q.size(); i++) begin\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t// Check mismatch status for this logged cycle\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t// Note: We re-evaluate the match status for logging clarity.\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t// Since the mismatch happened on the current clock edge, the state i-1 was correct, and i is incorrect.\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tif (golden_output_q[i] === got_output_q[i]) begin\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t$display(\\"Cycle %0d: Match Confirmed.\\", i);\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t// Since we only display on FIRST error, we stop detailed logging here for brevity.\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t// The original requirement is complex: "\n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n                \n       